cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.CC, cs.SD

The paper discusses the Generative Lexicon, which is a computational linguistic theory, and argues against Fodor and Lepore's attack on it. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also discusses Artificial Intelligence and semantic rules, which suggests cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as the second likely category. The paper also mentions the practical worth of computational systems, which could fall under cs.LG (Machine Learning) or cs.CC (Computational Complexity). Finally, the paper discusses the relationship of cultural representational structures to each other and to the world, which could fall under cs.SD (Sound).
